tched.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering event handling logic**\\n\\nI’m thinking about capturing `before = eventQueue.peekEvent()` after defaultDialog, but maybe that’s not necessary. I wonder if `getNextEvent()` will block when there are no events, which could be sufficient.\\n\\nHowever, what if an earlier event from `push` exists? It seems possible that dispatching one event might not account for the lambda scenario. I need to ensure the logic effectively handles all possible events without missing any significant ones. This could get a bit complex, but it’s important for robustness!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing AtomicInteger**\\n\\nI’m considering using the AtomicInteger import, and then I need to test and verify the dispatch of the defaultDialog runnable. I'll implement this and use assertThat for checking the error messages with the hasValue method. I'll need to import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger since existing patterns utilize hasValue. It feels like a good step, but I’m questioning whether it’s truly necessary. Maybe it’ll be helpful in the long run!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_TkA1fjTDRoLxIOyQWkJjw93J|fc_0e16fa176372072f0169f4cf77ba7c8192aebcc5f0f0fabd59", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_durian/durian_core/ErrorsInnerPluginsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\n", "newText": "import java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n"}, {"oldText": "        RuntimeException error = new RuntimeException(\"dialog fallback path\");\n", "newText": "        DialogTestException error = new DialogTestException(\"dialog fallback path\");\n"}, {"oldText": "            Errors.Plugins.defaultDialog(error);\n            eventQueue.dispatchNextEvent();\n", "newText": "            Errors.Plugins.defaultDialog(error);\n            int message