ues. The task might require an environment where AWT can run. I need to revisit previous attempts because being headless results in failures. Removing headless modes and adding an auto-closing timer seems necessary. I also wonder if Method.invoke captures errors when there’s no DISPLAY. The aim is to ensure coverage for scenarios with and without displays, so I need a design that handles both situations.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering AWT Toolkit solutions**\\n\\nI need to ensure a normal return even without a display. I wonder if we can set up a fake AWT Toolkit or GraphicsEnvironment through a public API, rather than using reflection. Could the `java.awt.graphicsenv` property help here? Creating a custom GraphicsEnvironment might work, but it loads at the system level. Is it feasible to set this up before the GraphicsEnvironment initialization? I’m also curious about dynamic class loading and if I can have a test class ready at build time.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing dialog behavior**\\n\\nI’m looking into how showMessageDialog works. It gets invoked on the Event Dispatch Thread (EDT) by Runnable, which starts a nested event loop with modal dialogs. This means the Swing Timer will fire within that nested loop, allowing it to dispose. I need to ensure that if there's nothing to display, the method returns quickly. I'll also be testing assertions to confirm that messageReads has increased and that the output has printed correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qtEw52Zzi8eQTw9NulXhXlck|fc_0e16fa176372072f0169f4d0af99248192bc06ae37a036656e", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_durian/durian_core/ErrorsInnerPluginsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.awt.AWTEvent;\nimport java.awt.EventQueue;\nimport java.awt.Toolkit;\n", "newText": "import java.awt.Window;\n"}, {"oldText": "import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n", "newText": "import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n\nimport javax.swing.SwingUtilities;\nimport javax.swing.Timer;\n"}, {"oldText": "        System.setProperty(\"java.awt.headless\", \"true\");\n        DispatchingEventQueue eventQueue = new DispatchingEventQueue();\n        Toolkit.getDefaultToolkit().getSystemEventQueue().push(eventQueue);\n\n        try (PrintStream replacementErr = new PrintStream(capturedErr, true, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)) {\n            System.setErr(replacementErr);\n\n            Errors.Plugins.defaultDialog(error);\n            int messageReadsAfterScheduling = error.messageReads();\n\n            eventQueue.dispatchUntilMessageReadIncreases(error, messageReadsAfterScheduling);\n\n            assertThat(error.messageReads()).isGreaterThan(messageReadsAfterScheduling);\n        } finally {\n            System.setErr(originalErr);\n            eventQueue.popQueue();\n            restoreSystemProperty(\"java.awt.headless\", previousHeadless);\n        }\n", "newText": "        Timer closeDialogs = new Timer(50, event -> disposeShowingWindows());\n        closeDialogs.setRepeats(true);\n\n        try (PrintStream replacementErr = new PrintStream(capturedErr, true, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)) {\n            enableAwtWhenDisplayIsAvailable();\n            System.setErr(replacementErr);\n            closeDialogs.start();\n\n            Errors.Plugins.defaultDialog(error);\n            int messageReadsAfterScheduling = error.messageReads();\n\n            SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(() -> assertThat(SwingUtilities.isEventDispatchThread()).isTrue());\n\n            assertThat(error.messageReads()).isGreaterThan(messageReadsAfterScheduling);\n        } finally {\n            closeDialogs.stop();\n            disposeShowingWindows();\n            System.setErr(originalErr);\n            restoreSystemProperty(\"java.awt.headless\", previousHeadless);\n        }\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class DispatchingEventQueue extends EventQueue {\n        private void dispatchUntilMessageReadIncreases(DialogTestException error, int previousReads)\n                throws InterruptedException {\n            long deadline = System.nanoTime() + TimeUnit.SECONDS.toNanos(5);\n            while (error.messageReads() <= previousReads && System.nanoTime() < deadline) {\n                AWTEvent event = peekEvent();\n                if (event == null) {\n                    Thread.sleep(10);\n                } else {\n                    dispatchEvent(getNextEvent());\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        private void popQueue() {\n            pop();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreSystemProperty(String propertyName, String previousValue) {\n", "newText": "    private static void enableAwtWhenDisplayIsAvailable() {\n        if (System.getenv(\"DISPLAY\") != null || System.getenv(\"WAYLAND_DISPLAY\") != null) {\n            System.setProperty(\"java.awt.headless\", \"false\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void disposeShowingWindows() {\n        for (Window window : Window.getWindows()) {\n            if (window.isShowing()) {\n                window.dispose();\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreSystemProperty(String propertyName, String previousValue) {\n"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.diffplug.durian/durian-core/1.2.0/src/test/java/com_diffplug_durian/durian_core/ErrorsInnerPluginsTest.java\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText\":\"import java.awt.AWTEvent;\\nimport java.awt.EventQueue;\\nimport java.awt.Toolkit;\\n\",\"newText\":\"import java.awt.Window;\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\\n\",\"newText\":\"import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\\n\\nimport javax.swing.SwingUtilities;\\nimport javax.swing.Timer;\\n\"},{\"oldText\":\"        System.setProperty(\\\"java.awt.headless\\\", \\\"true\\\